HEADWORD: Merchet
<hw>Mer"chet</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>
}</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL. <ets>marcheta</ets>; of uncertain
origin.]</ety> <def>In old English and in Scots law, a fine paid to the
lord of the soil by a tenant upon the marriage of one the tenant's
daughters.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

